   {
      "body" : "Fraudulent double-spending clearly harms the Bitcoin economy, so I would say miners have a light incentive to make an attempt to prevent it when practical. (Non-fraudulent double-spending does not, AFAIK, have any case harmed by this behaviour.)\r\n\r\nThere is a subtle risk to this behaviour I should document: if a transaction is the *cause* of the stale chain being non-best, we would not want to re-mine that transaction. I don't know if there's a good way to determine and prevent this.",
